{
  "texts": [
    "(Moslemipour et al., 2012) Machine learning approaches using neural networks (NN) can deliver fast decisions on complex problems and are robust against varying problem formulations.",
    "Solving the complex control tasks proves challenges when using preprogrammed agent behaviors.",
    "(Busoniu et al., 2008) Moreover, training data for these machine learning approaches, which is not available for control tasks in LMAS, is unnecessary when reinforcement learning (RL) is used.",
    "The planning and control of LMAS consists of two optimization problems (layout and scheduling).",
    "RL approaches are mainly limited to systems that focus on one a single task."
  ]
}